  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Production CrossRoads A Soap Opera for Social Change</narrative>
  </title>
  <description akvo:type="5" type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Cross Roads, a Soap Opera for Social Change, is an EU-funded programme with two co-applicants. Media Focus on Africa (MFA) is ICCO&apos;s key partner which developed the programme. TriVision Uganda was contracted to film and produce the series.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description akvo:type="6" type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">ICCO Cooperation worked with two partners in this programmes: Media Focus on Africa (MFA) and TriVision Uganda Ltd (Trivision). In 2014 and 2015, most activities had been carried out by MFA, though from the second 	half of 2015 Trivision became involved as the line producer. Because of the complexity of the project and to be able to provide adequate supervision, it was deemed necessary to separate the production of the series into two parts, whereby ICCO signed  a contract with Trivision as line producer, while MFA entered into a separate contract with one of Trivision&#xFFFD;&#xFFFD;&#xFFFD;s directors, Irene Kulabako, as the director of the series. 

The key player roles were therefore as follows:
ICCO: Contractor and supervisor of the line producer  
MFA: Advisory role on the progress of implementation of contract between Trivision and ICCO. MFA separately contracted the director of the series, Irene Kulabako.
Trivision: line producer and in charge of the production. 
Irene Kulabako: director of the series, contracted by MFA.</narrative>
  </description>
